Test Plan Output for Accuracy & Workflow Usage Documentation
1. Test Plan Output for Accuracy
The plan-only workflow is used to validate infrastructure changes before applying them to the environment. This ensures that proposed changes are reviewed and verified before execution.
Objective
Verify that the Terraform plan output correctly reflects the infrastructure changes without modifying any resources.
Test Steps
Trigger the plan-only workflow for the respective environment (dev, qa, prod).
Ensure the workflow runs successfully without applying changes.
Review the Terraform plan output generated in the pipeline logs.
Validation Checks
The following should be verified in the plan output:
Resource Creation
Confirm newly defined resources appear with + in the plan output.
Resource Modification
Confirm updates appear with ~ indicating configuration changes.
Resource Deletion
Confirm removed resources appear with -.
No Unexpected Changes
Ensure that unrelated infrastructure is not modified.
Environment Variables and Secrets
Verify that environment-specific variables are correctly picked up during execution.
Reusable Workflow Execution
Confirm that the plan workflow is executed via the reusable workflow configuration.
Glue Script Deployment Disabled
Ensure Glue script deployment steps are skipped during plan-only runs.
Expected Outcome
Terraform successfully generates the plan.
No infrastructure changes are applied.
Output clearly displays the proposed changes.
Pipeline completes successfully.
2. When to Use Plan vs Deploy Workflow
Plan Workflow
The Plan Workflow is used to preview infrastructure changes before applying them.
When to Use
Use the plan workflow in the following scenarios:
Before merging infrastructure changes.
During pull request validation.
When reviewing Terraform changes.
To verify configuration updates.
To ensure environment variables and modules behave correctly.
Behavior
Runs terraform init
Runs terraform plan
Displays proposed changes
Does NOT apply infrastructure changes
apply_changes = false
Deploy Workflow
The Deploy Workflow is used to apply infrastructure changes to the target environment.
When to Use
Use the deploy workflow in the following scenarios:
After Terraform plan has been reviewed and approved.
When changes need to be applied to infrastructure.
During scheduled or approved infrastructure releases.
After pull request merge.
Behavior
Runs terraform init
Runs terraform plan
Runs terraform apply
Applies infrastructure changes
apply_changes = true
